<HEADLINE> Beijing Gala Performance to Mark National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A grand theatrical show was
staged this evening in the Great Hall of the People here to mark
the 48th founding anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee Hu Jintao,
Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing watched the show together with an
audience of 10,000.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hall of the People was colorfully decorated for
China's National Day, which falls October 1. One slogan
read: "Holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory and
forging ahead the great course of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the 21st century in an all-round way".
</P>
<P>
The curtain was raised to the audience's singing of China's
National Anthem. Beijing Opera and dance items were performed and
songs were sung in praise of late leaders Mao Zedong and Deng
Xiaoping as well as the new leading collective with Party General
Secretary Jiang Zemin at its core.
</P>
<P>
Some performances were given to express the artists' happiness
about the return of Hong Kong to the motherland and the success of
the 15th CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
Renowned artists sang such selections as "China Reaps Harvest,"
"The Sun Never Sets on Grassland" and "Tomorrow Is A Better Day,"
describing a bright future under the CPC leadership and showing
China's ambitions to work miracles in the 21st century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
