<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Indian Visitors (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Echoing Deng Xiaoping's words
that China poses no threat to India nor is India a threat to
China, senior CPC leader Li Ruihan said today that the two countries
have every reason to deepen their friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the
comments during a meeting here with a delegation from the
Communist Party of India (CPI) led by its general secretary
Ardhendu Bardhan.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is also chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said
that China and India are neighbors, each with a long history and
splendid civilization. Both countries are engaged in developing
their economies and improving the quality of their respective
peoples, and share identical or similar viewpoints on many major
international issues.
</P>
<P>
On the history of the international communist movement, Li said
it was a necessity for the communist parties in some countries to
take power at the beginnging of the century. Similarly, there were
inner causes for the frustration of the communist movement in some
countries in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Both sides of the historical experience show that it is
imperative that the communist parties give priority to advancing
productive forces of the society and improving the living
standards of the people after they come to power, thus winning
support from the masses, he pointed out.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971001.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Indian Visitors (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said that the key reason the Communist Party of China stands
strong in the changing international situation is that
the Chinese communists, represented by Deng Xiaoping, carefully
sum up experience and learn from their past and draw on both the
successes and failures of other socialist countries.
</P>
<P>
The Party also has set the growth of productive forces of
the society as the basic task of the primary stage of socialism and
set forth the guidelines of "one central task, two basic points,"
namely, regarding economic advancement as the core, and sticking
to the four fundamental principles and reform and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
The practice over the past 18 years has fully proved that the
policies of the Communist Party of China are correct and Deng
Xiaoping Theory is also correct, he stated.
</P>
<P>
"Although we are faced with some difficulties, and there might
be some problems on the road ahead, our cause will prevail as long
as we follow Deng Xiaoping Theory," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Bardhan extended his congratulations on the successful
convening of the 15th CPC National Congress, and on the 48th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
He said that Li's words will help the Communist Party of India
understand the spirit of the 15th CPC National Congress, and
that his party highly appreciates all the decisions made at the
congress.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that practice has proven that the road initiated
by the Communist Party of China is correct, and that Deng
Xiaoping's theories that poverty is not socialism and economic
development is the prerequisite for consolidating and carrying
forward socialism have contributed to the development of
Marxism-Leninism.
</P>
<P>
Bardhan said that his party is ready to make concerted efforts
to advance friendly bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Dai Bingguo, head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Indian visitors, who are here as guests of the CPC, will
also travel to Nanchang and Shanghai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
