<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build Railway to Connect Xinjiang with Central Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A feasibility study was
completed today for the construction of a border railway, which will
be part of the new Asia-Europe Continental Bridge.
</P>
<P>
The railway will be built in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region to serve as an international outlet connecting
China and central Asian countries, said Er Xide, chief engineer of
the railway.
</P>
<P>
The 300-kilometer railway will have an annual transporting
capacity of 10 million tons, Er said. Construction
will start later next year and be completed in two years.
</P>
<P>
The railway will benefit a grain and cotton production base in
Yili Prefecture in west Xinjiang and largely ease the
transportation tension between China and central Asian countries,
he said.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
