<HEADLINE> CPC Ranking Official Meets Indian Visitors  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- China's great achievements in
reform and opening-up have proved that Marxism is the guiding
truth, Li Ruihuan, a ranking Communist Party of China (CPC) official,
told Harkishan Surjeet, general secretary of the Communist Party
of India (Marxist) today.
</P>
<P>
Li, both a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of
the CPC Central Committee and chairman of the National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC),
conveyed greetings from General Secretary of the CPC Central
Committee Jiang Zemin to Surjeet during their talks.
</P>
<P>
Li said China will continue to adhere to Marxism so as to
"overcome the difficulties on the road of advance and score
still greater success."
</P>
<P>
"The adherence that we are talking about is precisely the
adherence to the basic principles of Marxism," he noted. "The
development history of Marxism is a history of overcoming the
limitations of the predecessors and setting forth new viewpoints."
</P>
<P>
"To ignore development and only consider some outdated
conclusions is not genuine adherence to Marxism," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Li also mentioned that Lenin could not have brought forth
Leninism had he not proposed, in accordance with the reality of
Russia then, that socialism could succeed in a country where the
capitalism rule was the weakest.
</P>
<P>
Mao Zedong, he noted, could not have produced Mao Zedong
Thought had he not set forth, in line with China's revolutionary
practice at the time, the theory of encircling the cities from the
countryside and finally seizing them.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
