<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971001.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Ranking Official Meets Indian Visitors  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
And Deng Xiaoping could not have brought forth Deng Xiaoping
Theory if he did not correct some of Mao Zedong's conclusions or
creatively put forward a series of new theses in accordance with
the specific conditions in China's construction.
</P>
<P>
So it is imperative to continue to combine the cardinal
principles of Marxism with both a nation's specific conditions and
characteristics of an era, he noted. The combination should not
produce only a theoretical answer, but also a tangible development
-- only in this way will Marxism be full of vigor and vitality.
</P>
<P>
Surjeet said the report delivered by Jiang Zemin at the
15th CPC National Congress not only summarized China's experience,
but also summed up the course of the development of Marxism, which
is helpful to China and the cause of socialism in the world.
</P>
<P>
"We have always held that it is easy for the Communist parties
to build socialism after they come into power," he said, adding
that there are no ready-made answers for backward nations to build
socialism through Marxism.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping had made a major contribution in this regard, he
noted, saying that without growth of productive forces, socialism
could not be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
This is an arduous task for developing nations, and that the
theory of the primary stage of socialism set forth by the Chinese
communists is a new development of Marxism, Surjeet concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
