<HEADLINE> UNDP Planning Events to Mark International Day for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A series of events
organized by the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) will
take place in cities around the world on October 17, the
International Day for the Eradication of Poverty, to draw
attention to the widespread presence of poverty and its
debilitating effects on humanity.
</P>
<P>
In New York, UNDP's Division of Public Affairs(DPA) will
sponsor a major event on that day at the UN, hosted by actor Danny
Glover. Individuals from El Salvador, South Africa, Viet Nam and
the US will be recognized for their work in poverty eradication.
</P>
<P>
Around the world, UNDP country offices are helping organizing
local debates and press conferences, school essay and art
contests, and cultural and sporting events to raise awareness of
poverty.
</P>
<P>
October 17 has been designated the International Day for the
Eradication of Poverty by the UN General Assembly to generate
awareness and mobilize action against poverty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
