<HEADLINE> Courier Enters Second Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- American former world number
one Jim Courier moved into the second round of the China Open on
Tuesday by beating Alex Radulescu of Germany 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Courier, who has clinched 20 singles titles in his tennis
career, will meet Patrik Fredrikson of Sweden, who ousted fourth
seed Marcos Ondruska of South Africa 5-7, 6-3, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Courier broke three times before he beat Radulescu,
No. 68 in the world who lost to his countryman Nicolas Kiefer in
the Toulouse Open semifinals in France last week.
</P>
<P>
"I'm satisfied with my first match in China," said Courier, who
was the world No.1 in 1992.
</P>
<P>
"I hope to win the singles here, but now the most important for
me is next round." He also said: "If I keep the form as I was in
1992, I could take over the world number one someday. However,
it's very difficult."
</P>
<P>
Kiefer, winner of the Toulouse Open Sunday by beating the
reigning champion Mark Philippoussis of Australia, will meet Renzp
Furlan of Italy in Wednesday's clash which was postponed for his
delay on the way from France to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"I feel good," said Kiefer in France. "But I'm pretty tired. I
hope to give my best in Beijing, but I will see what happens."
</P>
