Police Chiefs Cooperation (sarpcco) extraordinary meeting in
Harare.
</P>
<P>
''Sarpcco, therefore, provides the pillar on which the success
of all other forms of integration rest as we all look forward to
take full advantage and maximize the benefits of the existing
peace within the region,'' said Dabengwa.
</P>
<P>
The fruits of cooperation in the fight against cross border
crime, the minister noted, were beginning to be seen.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,576 stolen vehicles were recovered during the
first phase of Voyager Four operation, an exercise aimed at
dealing with cross border vehicle thefts.
</P>
<P>
A total of 143 car theft suspects were arrested under the
operation which involved Mozambique, South Africa, Zambia and
Zimbabwe. 
