<HEADLINE> US Returns Cuban Hijackers to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The United States will
send home two Cubans who hijacked a border patrol boat and took
four people hostage in an attempt to go to the U.S., the State
Department announced today.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the two Cubans seized a wooden vessel along the
Cuban island's north coast, fending off a pursuing patrol boat
with gunfire.
</P>
<P>
The hijacked vessel managed to escape despite substantial
damage, said State Department spokesman James Rubin.
</P>
<P>
The hijackers and the four hostages were picked up by the U.S.
Coast Guard off the Florida Keys Thursday and were taken to the
U.S. Naval Base at Guantanamo Bay.
</P>
<P>
All the hostages, a teenager girl and three border guard
personnel, were returned to Cuba Monday and the hijackers will
soon be sent back, Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
Cuba has asked the hijacked vessel and the hijackers to be
returned to Cuban custody. 
</P>
