<HEADLINE> European Shares Up, London Hits New Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 30 (Xinhua) -- All the three major stock
markets in Europe ended higher today, with London setting a new
record closing high, but off their session highs on weaker Wall
Street.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index ended the last day of the month at
another record high despite late downward pressure from Wall
Street. The market was also boosted by support for European
monetary union from Labor Party members. The index closed at
5,244.2, up 23.9 points.
