German shares in Frankfurt closed sharply higher in response to
the firm dollar and Wall Street's overnight advance. Chemical and
industrial stocks were encouraged by the dollar's rebound.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index finished the session 63.58 points higher at
4,167.85.
</P>
<P>
On the Paris bourse, the CAC-40 index closed up 19.30 points
and back over the 3,000-point level at 3,008.26 on the back of
other European markets. 
