<HEADLINE> Chinese National Day Marked in African Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese embassies in some
African countries held receptions today to mark the birthday of
the People's Republic of China which falls on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador to Uganda Tan Xingju gave a reception in
Kampala this evening to celebrate the 48th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The year of 1997 witnessed smooth return of Hong Kong to its
motherland and the convening of the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China, Tan said.
</P>
<P>
