<HEADLINE> Goldberger Fined for Cocaine Possession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Triple World Cup ski jump
champion Andreas Goldberger, temporarily suspended from the
Austrian team for using cocaine, was Wednesday ordered to pay a
fine for "multiple possession" of the drug.
</P>
<P>
The court did not immediately announce the amount of the fine.
</P>
<P>
Goldberger was suspended by the Austrian Ski Federation in
April, a day after admitting trying cocaine "just once" at a
Viennese disco last year.
</P>
<P>
Goldberger, whose form dipped this season after World Cup
triumphs in 1993, 1995 and 1996, admitted trying the drug on
Austrian television following widespread rumours in the Austrian
media.
</P>
<P>
Goldberger has said he still intends to compete at next year's
Winter Olympics.  
