<HEADLINE> Torch Relay for National Games Held in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A torch relay and the flag
presentation ceremony for the Hong Kong delegation to the Eighth
Chinese National Games were held here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Fenella Ng, a local sportswoman, ignited the torch and passed
it to Timothy Fok, head of the Hong Kong delegation for the Eighth
National Games in the Hong Kong Sports Institute.
</P>
<P>
After receiving the torch from Fok, Chau Tak-hay, Secretary for
Broadcasting, Culture and Sports Bureau of Hong Kong, handed it to
Arthur Li, a famous Hong Kong swimmer.
</P>
<P>
Li, accompanied by other athletes and representatives from 18
districts of Hong Kong, finished the one lap run in the institute
and carried the torch on board a ship to head for the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center, where he passed the torch to
Tung Chee-hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
Tung officially handed the torch to Fok. The torch will be
taken to Shanghai to join the torches from China's other
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions for the opening
ceremony of the games which are scheduled to be held on October 12.
</P>
<P>
Following the torch relay, Tung, on behalf of the government of
the HKSAR, presented a flag of the HKSAR to representatives of the
delegation.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong will send a 260-member delegation to the Eighth
National Games, the ever largest since Hong Kong began
participating in large scale games.  
</P>
</TEXT>
