<HEADLINE> Manila Creates Task Forces to Address Economic, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Ramos today
created two inter-agency task forces which will formulate and
recommend measures to address the country's economic and
environmental problems.
</P>
<P>
The first is the Task Force for the Currency Situation and
Related Economic Concerns chaired by both Finance Secretary
Roberto de Ocampo and Trade Secretary Cesar Bautista.
</P>
<P>
Ramos directed the task force to recommend measures and
formulate the necessary economic policies, including legislative
actions, that will enable the country to cope with the currency
situation, stabilize the Philippine economy and get it back on a
stable track.
</P>
<P>
He also ordered it to conduct consultations and elicit the
views and recommendations of the private sector and other
concerned sectors on how the present socio-economic concerns may
be addressed.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the Philippine Central Bank and the
private sector should be invited as members of the task force.
</P>
<P>
The second was the Task Force for El Nino Phenomenon chaired by
both Environment Secretary Victor Ramos and Agriculture Secretary
Salvador Escudero.
</P>
<P>
The El Nino task force will serve as the coordinating body for
the effective implementation of measures to mitigate the adverse
impact of the El Nino phenomenon on the country, particularly on
the environment and agriculture.  
</P>
