<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Young People Spend National Day in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 1,000 young people from
Hong Kong spent their first National Day in the Chinese capital
after the region returned to the motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
They are the first group of the 10,000 Hong Kong yougsters
organized by the Hong Kong Soong Ching Ling Fund to visit the
inland areas, for the purpose of better understanding China.
</P>
<P>
In the morning they visited the residence of Soong Ching Ling,
wife of China's revolutionary pioneer Sun Yat-sen, in northern
downtown Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"We knew little about Soong Ching Ling previously. But now we
understand that she was an important historical figure of our
country," said Chen Shuxian, a student.
</P>
<P>
During the War of Resistance against Japan (1937-45), Soong
stayed in Hong Kong to raise funds and materials to support the
Chinese army.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that after visiting the house, she knew that Soong
had made many contributions to the development of China by serving
the Chinese people wholeheartedly.
</P>
<P>
Chen Songde, another student, said that Soong was not only the
wife of Sun Yat-sen, but also Sun's comrade-in-arms and the
inheritor of his revolutionary cause. "She is one of the greatest
women in the 20th century," he said.
</P>
<P>
The young people will tour Beijing for the next several days.
</P>
