<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Gives Reception for National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive
 of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), held a
large-scale reception here this afternoon to celebrate the 48th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception with participation of some 5,000
people, Tung said that he was deeply moved while attending the
first flag-rising ceremony here earlier this morning, because Hong
Kong had finally returned to the motherland and Hong Kong people
had truly become the masters of their own destiny.
</P>
<P>
"We for the first time to celebrate our National Day as
citizens of the SAR," he said, adding that "I am saluting to our
motherland in the name of the SAR people."
</P>
<P>
He said that as a Chinese he was very proud of the motherland's
great achievements in the social, political and economic spheres
and of its important position in the international arena.
</P>
<P>
On July 1 this year, Hong Kong returned to the motherland and
entered a new era of its history, Tung said, noting that the SAR
government has successfully operated since then. The economic
development and citizens' life style have been as they were
before, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We have witnessed continuing vitality, prosperity and
stability in our society," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
He stated that the SAR government will continue to make its
contributions to keeping prosperity and stability in Hong Kong, a
part of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"Let me take this joyous occasion to wish our nation continuing
success in its development, and an even brighter and better future
for Hong Kong's people," he said.
</P>
<P>
Present at the reception were Ann Tse-kai and Henry Fok
Ying-tung, both vice-chairmen of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), Jiang
Enzhu, director of Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch, Ma Yuzhen,
commissioner of the Chinese Foreign Ministry, and Liu Zhenwu,
commander of the Chinese People's Liberation Army Garrison in the
Hong Kong SAR.
