<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Madagascar Sign Air Services Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Madagascar
today signed here an agreement on air services.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed by Malaysian Transport Minister Ling
Liong Sik and his Madagascar counterpart Rama Monjisoa
Andrianaivo, designated airlines are entitled to operate a daily
service between Malaysia and Madagascar.
</P>
<P>
Ling said after the signing ceremony that the air services to
Madagascar would not start immediately although both parties had
signed the agreement.
</P>
<P>
He said airlines from both countries could first work on
exchanging passengers via intermediate or beyond points and once
there was sufficient number of passengers, then a direct link
would start.
</P>
<P>
Ling said Malaysia's determination to have an air link to
Madagascar was under the auspices of the South-South Cooperation
which was strongly promoted by the Malaysian government.
</P>
