<DOCNO> XIE19971001.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Begins Regulating Commercial Theatrical Performances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A set of regulations on
improving the management of commercial theatrical performances
went into effect today in China.
</P>
<P>
The regulations, issued by the State Council, stipulate that
performances must adhere to the principle of serving the people
and socialism, and must not have a negative social impact.
</P>
<P>
Commercial performances have become the main form of China's
theatrical production. Some of the stage shows have mediocre
scripts with vulgar content, and some actors have demanded
exorbitant salaries and have evaded taxes, according to an
official from the Ministry of Culture.
</P>
<P>
The regulations note that the performances should promote the
quality of national arts and enrich the cultural life of the
people. The content of advertisements must be both truthful and
legal, and must in no way deceive consumers.
</P>
<P>
According to the regulations, China will not allow the
establishment in China of joint-venture or solely
overseas-funded theatrical troupes, performing venues and
brokering institutions.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment is allowed for the establishment or
renovation of theaters, but those investors are not allowed to
participate in the management or operation of the theaters, the
regulations said.
</P>
<P>
If artists from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Macao,
Taiwan of China or from other countries want to produce commercial
performances in China, they must receive approval from the
Ministry of Culture and are required to be managed by brokering
institutions.
</P>
<P>
The ministry official said that after the regulations are
implemented, cultural departments at various levels should
organize cadres and workers to study the new rules, and intensive
projects to regulate the cultural market will be carried out.
</P>
<P>
China has 57,000 theatrical troupes and 400 brokering agencies
providing services and information in the field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971001.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
