late yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Late today, gold was trading at higher at 335.05 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"The retracement levels on the Aussie are now going to be
limited with bullion looking very solid, copper looking very
solid," said Guy Reynolds, foreign exchange manager with Macquarie
Bank.
</P>
<P>
"It was a terrific move today and the target is now 73.10 U.S.
cents, a level we have been looking at for quite some time," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Traders said also underpinning the currency on the day was the
fact that many players now think any rate cut by the Reserve Bank
of Australia is not likely to occur until late October or early
November.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 1.2784 marks, from 1.34 here
previously.
</P>
<P>
Against the yen, the local unit was at 87.53, off an intraday
high of 88.49, after closing yesterday at 87.21. 
