<HEADLINE> China's Adhesive Output Increases Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- China's output of adhesives and
sealants will hit two million to 2.4 million tons annually by
2000, sources said.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of an international adhesives exhibition said that
growth averaging 16 percent a year between 1985 and 1996 has given
the country's synthetic adhesive industry an annual production
capacity of 1.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
They said that the increased production of adhesives can be
attributed to the fast-growing automotive and construction
industries.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, to run from October 8 to 10 at the National
Agricultural Exhibition Hall, will showcase the latest development
in the sector. A total of 2,000 adhesive products will be on
display, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Some 20 foreign exhibitors including international chemical
giants as BASF, Bayer, 3M Exxon and Mitsucoctoc will participate
in the event.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is organized by the China National Adhesives
Industry Association and the China Council for Promotion of
International Trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
