<HEADLINE> Iranian President Calls for Active Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami today called for active exchanges of information and
technology in the world.
</P>
<P>
The president made the call while addressing the opening
ceremony of the 23rd Tehran International Trade Fair, which draws
1,100 firms from 63 countries.
</P>
<P>
Khatami stated "countries' attempts to achieve development and
progress is a giant stride towards achieving real peace in the
world."
</P>
<P>
While calling for active exchange of information and
technology, the Iranian president also criticized attempts by some
countries to monopolize science and technology.
</P>
<P>
"If we long for a safe and stable world, we need to create a
just environment granting all human beings access to information,
science and technology."
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said the fair serves to create proper atmosphere
for exchange of scientific, technical and industrial know-how to
accelerate the development of the country.
</P>
<P>
The fair will continue till October 9. This year over 1,720
local companies are exhibiting manufactured, industrial and
commercial goods at the fair.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the fair say that the objectives are to
present capabilities of local companies in designing and
manufacturing various goods and reach international markets through
negotiations with foreign firms. 
