<HEADLINE> Macao Residents More Enthusiastic About National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Macao residents have become ever
more enthusiastic about China's National Day this year following
the success of Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
As major buildings and streets are awash with colorful flags
and red lanterns, local residents are holding more gatherings,
receptions, tea parties, and singing and dancing parties to mark
China's National Day.
</P>
<P>
Editorials in local newspapers cited this year's national
day as a special one worth of big celebration.
</P>
<P>
As a well-known businessman Ma Man Kei, chairman of the
presidium of the Macao Compatriots Preparatory Committee for the
Celebration of the 48th Anniversary of the Founding of the
People's Republic of China, put it, Hong Kong's return and the
15th Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) made this year
special.
</P>
<P>
"The successful return of Hong Kong has wiped out the
humiliation China suffered a century ago," he said in a speech at
a grand gathering today. "And the 15th Party Congress concluded
last month has laid an all-out plan for China's growth in the 21st
century."
</P>
<P>
More than 1,300 representatives from grassroots organizations,
leading social bodies as well as local residents, attended the
gathering, which staged singing and dancing performances as
celebration.
</P>
<P>
Similar gatherings, receptions, tea parties, dancing and
singing performances have increased notably this year as a way to
praise China, observers said.
</P>
<P>
Many residents said that they are happy because they have gained
confidence that under the policy of "one country, two systems",
Macao will also enjoy a better future as good as Hong Kong after
its return in a little more than two years time.
</P>
<P>
"China and Portugal have been cooperating well," said a leader
of the Macao Federation of Trade Unions. "Transitional affairs in
Macao are being resolved one by one and the process is being
quickened. We anticipated a smooth return in 1999 so long as
such trend continues."
</P>
<P>
Top Chinese officials stationed in Macao have said earlier
that the preparatory work for the return of Macao is "in full
swing and good order." The preparatory committee for the
establishment of the Macao Special Administrative Region is
expected to be set up early next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
