<HEADLINE> HK People Confident in Hong Kong's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A latest poll conducted by
Hong Kong University showed that a record-high 85 percent of
people have confidence in Hong Kong's future, a local newspaper
reported today.
</P>
<P>
And 68 percent of the respondents are confident about the "one
country, two systems" concept, according to the Ming Pao Daily
News.
</P>
<P>
The Social Sciences Research Center of the university has
conducted a monthly poll since April this year, which sees the
confidence level edging up continuously, said a researcher in
charge of the polls.
</P>
<P>
As to the concept of "one country, two systems," he said, Hong
Kong people have always been bullish over it, with optimism fueled
by repeated pledges by Chinese leaders.
</P>
<P>
According to another telephone poll by the paper, the
popularity of Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the government of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), has also
increased compared with two months ago.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 percent of the respondents agreed that Tung, who
assumed the post three months ago, has passed his "probation
period." 
</P>
