<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Uganda's Budding Cocoa Industry Makes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(by Cai Guozhong)
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's cocoa industry has
made much headway in recent years with cocoa export is
expected to reach 2,500 tons in the 1997/98 season in
comparision with 2,200 tons in the 1995/96 season.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture predicted that Uganda's cocoa
exports will increase from 2,200 tons in 1995/96 season to 2,500
tons in 1997/98 season.
</P>
<P>
Foreign exchange the country will get from the expotation of
cocoa this year will increase to 3.75 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's cocoa commercial export started in 1917, 16 years
later when cocoa was introduced into the country by Europeans and
Asians. However, the production of cocoa has been very low for
the past several decades.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics from the Agricultural Ministry in
June 1994, cocoa plantation covers 10,843 hectares in Uganda's
nine districts.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan government decided a few years ago to take steps
to develop the cocoa production. A cocoa development project was
worked out by the Ministry of Agriculture with an aim to reshape
the industry. The United States Agency For International
Development (USAID) under the Agri-Business Development Centre
(ADC) and the Investment Developing Export Agriculture (IDEA)
decided last year to fund the cocoa development project for the
next three years.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture worked to develop the cocoa
production by adaptive research, importation of improved cocoa
varieties and the provision of direct and indirect channels for
the transfer of expertise technology to the cocoa farmers.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the project also aims at training farmers in
cocoa growing areas, rehabilitation of the abandoned farms and
establishing cocoa nurseries countrywide.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the project, 20 nurseries countrywide are
to be set up in the country to supply farmers with improved
seedlings which produce high yields.
</P>
<P>
In order to fight vermin which will destroy cocoa, a
consultant on vermin has been invited to study the insect's
movement and eating habits, so as to fight it effectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
