<HEADLINE> Soeharto: Legislative, Executive Bodies Are Equal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
said today that the legislative and executive bodies of government
should have equal positions to enable the former to supervise the
implementation of the nation's development.
</P>
<P>
"To address the increasingly complex challenges in the future,
we must have legislative and executive institutions which function
to the optimum," he said after attending the swearing-in
ceremonies of the members of the People's Consultative Assembly at
the parliament building.
</P>
<P>
The assembly, which consists of all 500 members of the House of
Representatives and another 500 members chosen from various walks
of life, will serve for the 1997-2002 period.
</P>
<P>
The 1,000-member assembly will meet to elect the country's next
president and vice president in March next year.
</P>
<P>
The new house and assembly were the result of the 1997 general
election held on May 29, which was the sixth general election in
Indonesia under the aegis of the 1945 constitution.
</P>
<P>
The assembly is strongly dominated by the ruling party Golkar,
with 488 members, the powerful armed forces faction have 113
members, the United Development Party (PPP) 134, and the
Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI) 16.
</P>
<P>
To ensure that the national system will work properly, the
political, economic, socio-cultural and defense-security
infrastructures would work well too, the president said.
</P>
<P>
"Political parties, functional group, the social organizations,
the economic agencies, the artists and literati, even the
segments, groups and individual citizen must have an adequate room
for developing their creativity and initiative," he added.
</P>
<P>
Many politicians and analysts here predicted that the assembly
just sworn in this morning is likely to reelect the incumbent
76-year-old president for a seventh five-year term in March.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow, the assembly will elect a new speaker for the
1997-2002 period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
