Minister Magnus Malan, former Law and Order Minister Adriaan Vlok
and former Secretary of the State Security Council Pierre van der
Westhuizen.
</P>
<P>
Former Foreign Minister Pik Botha had accepted invitation to
the hearing.
</P>
<P>
Three generals and one admiral of the former South African
armed forces had been subpoenaed to appear at the TRC's special
hearing on the role of the armed forces during the apartheid
years. The hearings will take place in Cape Town next week.
</P>
<P>
In addition, former African National Congress's military
leader and now Defense Minister Joe Modise, his deputy Ronnie
Kasrils and Transport Minister Mac Maharaj will also give
evidence at the armed forces hearing. 
