<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Military Base in Turkey Closed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A U.S.-Turkish military base
which was built in southeastern Turkey to monitor the former
Soviet Union and the Middle East countries 41 years ago was closed
Tuesday, local Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Pirinclik Base in Turkish province of Diyarbakir has served
out its Cold War mission, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the U.S. personnel working in the base had returned
home and all the facilities had been dismantled and sent back to
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Some 280 Turkish staff employed by the base have also been
disbanded.
</P>
<P>
The Seventh Turkish Army Corps will use the Pirinclik as
one of its military bases, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
