<HEADLINE> Xinhua Hong Kong Branch Chief's Good Wishes to HK Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Enzhu, director of
Xinhua News Agency's Hong Kong Branch, expressed his best
wishes to Hong Kong residents on the occasion of the National
Day, in a written message circulated here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said in the message that not long ago, descendants of the
Chinese nation throughout the world celebrated the event of the
century -- the return of Hong Kong to its motherland.
</P>
<P>
"The smooth transition of Hong Kong, the smooth transfer of
power and the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) of the People's Republic of China,
marks the beginning of a new era in Hong Kong's history," he said.
</P>
<P>
Now, he went on to say, "we are celebrating the jubilant
occasion of the 48th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China." This is of special significance for Hong Kong
residents, as this is the first time for them to celebrate the
National Day together with people in other parts of China after
Hong Kong's return, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to take this opportunity to express my most
sincere festive greetings and send my best wishes" to all Hong
Kong residents, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return has rendered closer the relationship between
Hong Kong and the inland areas of China, Jiang said, adding that
their mutual support and common progress will achieve greater
success.
</P>
<P>
China's vast inland areas serve as a huge market for Hong
Kong's economic development while the return of Hong Kong will
provide better opportunities for international investors to enter
the market of China's inland areas and for the integration of the
Chinese economy with that of the world, the message said.
</P>
<P>
The recent successful convocation of the annual meetings of the
World Bank and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) in Hong Kong
has made a positive impact on consolidating and strengthening Hong
Kong's status as an international financial center, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The fact that Premier Li Peng and Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji
attended the meetings fully demonstrated that the Chinese central
government supported and attached great importance to the
meetings, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Under the guidance of "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong
people governing Hong Kong" and high-degree autonomy, and with the
backing of the ever stronger motherland, Hong Kong compatriots
will, under the leadership of the SAR government headed by Tung
Chee Hwa, "act as their own masters and give full play to their
talents," Jiang concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
