<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netherlands Donates Fund for Uganda Street Kids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Dutch government has
decided to donate 250,000 U.S. dollars this month to support
street children in Uganda, local daily The Monitor reported
today.
</P>
<P>
El-Wmbi, program manager of the Friends of Children
Association (FOCA) in Uganda was quoted as saying that the money
is meant to curtail the rising number of children on the street
by sensitizing society, facilitating them to undergo occupational
and vocational skills training and to facilitate FOCA
intervention through counselling and resetting street children.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs show
that there are about 2,000 children living on the streets of
Kampala, capital of Uganda, most of whom are orphans due to the
AIDS pandemic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
