<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
rallied in busy trading today.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 18 points higher at 2,572 with a
turnover of nearly 62 million NZ dollars (40 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Paper was the big mover of the day, up 22 cents to 330
cents on news that it had sold a Canadian paper mill. Also higher
were Telecom, rising 5c to 797c, Carter Holt Harvey, gaining 4c to
343c and Brierley Investment, climbing 3c to 138c.
</P>
<P>
Among other leaders, Air New Zealand dipped 3c to 277c and Lion
Nathan was stable at 382c.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 49 rises and 40 falls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
