<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lincoln National Looking To Enter China's Insurance Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Stephen T. Meldrum, the
president of Lincoln National China Co., Ltd, says that China's
booming insurance market has great potential because of the
sustained economic growth and social welfare reforms.
</P>
<P>
Meldrum spoke at a recent seminar on co-operation between
Chinese and American insurers held in Tianjin. The two-day seminar
was sponsored by Lincoln National of the United States and the
Tianjin Association of Insurers. Nearly 150 representatives of
Chinese insurance companies, governmental departments,
universities, and financial research institutes attended the
seminar.
</P>
<P>
China's insurance market has grown a great deal in the past few
years. In eastern coastal areas, the better-off people there have
shown greater interest in life and property insurance.
</P>
<P>
Lincoln National hopes to play an important role in China's
booming insurance market, and has opened representative offices in
Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangzhou, and invested a total of 80
million US dollars in China, said Meldrum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
