<HEADLINE> Colombian-Chinese Friendship to be Further Enhanced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Colombian
President Ernesto Samper Pizano said here today that Colombia will
open a consulate in China's city of Shanghai and a trade office in
Beijing next year.
</P>
<P>
Samper made the remarks at a reception given by the Chinese
embassy to Colombia to celebrate the 48th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian president highlighted the friendly ties between
the two countries, saying that the Colombian-Chinese friendship
will certainly be consolidated and strengthened in the future.
</P>
<P>
About 500 dignitaries including Colombian president, several
ministers, and representatives from all walks of life and overseas
Chinese in Colombia attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador to Colombia Huang Shikang briefed all the
guests on China's development in the past 48 years.
</P>
<P>
The new leadership of China with President Jiang Zemin at the
core was elected at the just-concluded 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China, Huang said.
</P>
<P>
Under the leadership of the new leading group, Chinese people
will unswervingly march on along the path of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics and reform and opening up to the
outside world, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government will do its utmost to further
consolidate and develop the friendly and cooperative ties between
China and Colombia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
