<HEADLINE> India, Spain Sign Treaty on Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 1 (Xinhua) -- India and Spain have signed an
investment promotion and protection agreement to infuse new
dynamism to the Indian-Spanish economic relations, the local press
said today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here on Tuesday by Indian Finance
Minister P. Chidambaram and visiting Spanish Deputy Prime Minister
and Minister of Economy and Finance Rodrigo Rato Figaredo.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, each country is required to encourage and
create favorable conditions for investors and to accord fair and
equitable treatment to investments from the other country.
</P>
