<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan-UK Accord on Freezing Ill-gotten Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is likely to sign an
agreement with Britain for the confiscation of assets of the
corrupt acquired through illegal means, local official sources
said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement titled "Avoidance of Corruption Agreement" is
possible to be signed within days, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the agreement was a bid to confiscate assets
of Pakistan's former prime minister Benazir Bhutto in the United
Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
However, said the sources, it remained a formidable task to
prove that the assets of Bhuttos in the UK were acquired through
illegal means.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the Pakistani government was holding
negotiations with the British government for pursuing the attempt
to freeze the accounts of Benazir and her husband Asif Ali
Zardari.
</P>
<P>
About the response of the British government regarding seizure
of the accounts of Benazir and Zardari as demanded by the
Pakistani government, the sources said that "we are optimistic
about the seizure as the response from the other side is very
positive."
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani government has already frozen accounts of Bhuttos
in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the agreement will also cover confiscation of assets
of corrupt UK citizens who may flee to Pakistan, the sources said.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
