<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Delivers National Day Message </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 1 (Xinhua) -- "The 48th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China is particularly
significant as we celebrate our National Day for the first time as
citizens of the Special Administrative Region (SAR)," SAR Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa said.
</P>
<P>
In a message carried by English newspapers here today, Tung
said, With the lapse of almost 100 days since Hong Kong's return
to China, "we have witnessed continuing vitality, prosperity and
stability in our society."
</P>
<P>
"We in Hong Kong take tremendous pride in our Chinese identity.
This is our home and we will move forward together to promote
prosperity of our country and the SAR," he continued.
</P>
<P>
"Let me take this joyous occasion to wish our nation
continuing success in its development, and an even brighter and
better future for Hong Kong's people," he concluded.  
</P>
