<HEADLINE> Moldovan President Meets Chinese NPC Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The friendship between
China and Moldova is a good example between a big country and a
small one, Moldova President Peter Luchinsky told a delegation of
the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) today.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with the Chinese NPC delegation headed by Yang
Zhenya, vice-chairman of the NPC's Foreign Affairs Committee in
Kishinev, Moldova's capital, Luchinsky said that relations between
Moldova and China are based on complete equality and that the two
countries have no difference.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Moldova's support for the Chinese government's
position on Taiwan, which he said is an inseparable part of China.
</P>
<P>
Dumitru Motpan, president of the Moldovan parliament, also met
the Chinese delegation Monday. 
</P>
