<HEADLINE> Bomb threat Forces HK-Bound Jet to Return to Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong-bound Philippine
Airlines jet flew back to Manila today after receiving a bomb
threat while it was airborne, the Philippine Air Transportation
Office said.
</P>
<P>
The office said that the PAL 747 TURBO jet 300 flew back to the
Ninoy Aquino International Airport in Manila a few minutes after
taking off when its pilot was informed by the Manila Control Tower
that a bomb was planted inside the plane.
</P>
<P>
It said 443 passengers and crew members disembarked from the
plane as airport security men with bomb sniffing dogs scoured the
jet for the bomb.
</P>
<P>
The office quoted sources at the aviation security command as
saying that the threat, which turned out negative, could have been
made by a prankster.
</P>
<P>
Last month, over 40 bomb threats were reported in Manila, but
so far the police had failed to determine who were responsible for
the hoaxes.  
</P>
