<HEADLINE> China Restates Stand on Peaceful Nuclear Utilization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The International Atomic
Energy Agency (IAEA) should pay due attention to the just demand
of the developing countries for peaceful nuclear utilization, a
Chinese official said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the IAEA annual conference, Chinese representative
Jiang Xinxiong said that in preventing nuclear proliferation, the
world body should not neglect the just demand of its members,
particularly the developing countries, to use nuclear energy for
peaceful purposes.
</P>
<P>
More importantly, he said, the IAEA should not restrict or
jeopardize the peaceful utilization of nuclear technology and the
development of nuclear energy industry in the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, director of China's State Atomic Energy Agency, noted
that keeping a proper balance between IAEA's two major tasks of
tightening inspections and promoting peaceful utilization is not
only a correct direction for the agency's future work but also a
foundation for its existence and growth.
</P>
<P>
Founded 40 years ago, the IAEA now has 127 member states and
has become most instrumental in promoting the peaceful use of
nuclear energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
