<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Gary Locke, the first
Chinese-American elected governor in the United States, is
starting a journey back to his ancestral home this week.
</P>
<P>
Locke, the Washington governor, will be accompanied by his
parents, brother and several sisters to his ancestral village of
Jilong in Guangdong province, which will become the highlight of
his 12-day Asia trip starting on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Locke's victory in the U.S. state elections last November, was
noticed in Jilong, his press secretary Marylou Flynn said. His
photos and news clippings of his political success were put up on
a wall in the village.
