China recently under the headlines: "Gary Locke, American Dream."
</P>
<P>
His Asia trip will certainly generate interest on both sides of
the Pacific Ocean and Boeing Co. officials hope his stay in China
will provide an opportunity for China to announce a major order
for commercial airliners.
</P>
<P>
Locke will take his first stop in Japan, then fly to Shanghai
to open a Washington state trade office. After that, he will go to
Beijing to meet Chinese leaders.
</P>
