<HEADLINE> HKSAR Holds 1st National Day Flag-Raising Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 1 (Xinhua) -- A solemn flag-raising ceremony
was held here early this morning to celebrate the 48th National
Day of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
This was the first official flag-raising ceremony in Hong Kong
dedicated to the Chinese National Day since the city returned to
the motherland on July 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 people gathered early this morning at the
seafront site at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center
Extension to watch the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony began at 8:00 a.m. A band played the Chinese
national anthem to accompany the raising of the flag. When the
five-star red flag slowly rose to the top of the 14.7-meter-high
post, the audience gave an enthusiastic applause and waved small
red flags in excitement.
</P>
<P>
"It's really a happy moment," said an 86-year-old Mr. Meng, who
 got up early and arrived at the spot before 7:00. "This is our
first National Day celebration, I did not want to miss it."
</P>
<P>
After watching the ceremony, a Mr. He, in his 60s, and his wife
 had a picture taken in front of the flag post as a memento.
</P>
<P>
"We are glad to see the raising of our national flag," He
said. "You can see that Hong Kong has been doing very well since
it became a special administrative region (SAR) and we are very
confident in our future."
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference Henry Fok Ying-tung, Chief Executive of HKSAR Tung Chee
Hwa, Director of Xinhua News Agency HK Branch Jiang Enzhu and many
other government officials and local celebrities were also present
at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said that starting from today, a
flag-raising ceremony will be held everyday on the same
spot. 
