<HEADLINE> Malaysian Ringgit Opens at Historical Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's currency, the
ringgit, today opened at a historical low of 3.2820/70 against the
U.S. dollar since the local unit was floated in 1973.
</P>
<P>
The ringgit, which hit new lows during the past three days,
closed at 3.2405/55 yesterday against the greenback.
</P>
<P>
The new lows were due to nervousness over the market's
direction following the downtrend in regional currencies, a dealer
said.
</P>
<P>
Most players, especially locals in the commercial sector, are
holding short positions on dollars due to its appreciation, he
added.
</P>
<P>
They are anticipating for some good news in the upcoming
budget, which is scheduled to be announced on October 17, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ringgit is expected to trade within a range of 3.27 to 3.30
against the greenback today, the dealer added.
</P>
<P>
The local unit was also lower today against the Singapore
dollar, at 2.1247/93 from yesterday's 2.1152/99, against the
Japanese yen (100) at 2.7042/94 from 2.6715/67, against the
Deutsche mark at 1.8556/95 from 1.8300/33 as well as against pound
sterling at 5.2947/44 from 5.2279/92.  
</P>
</TEXT>
