<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Hold International Industrial Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 1 (Xinhua) -- An international industrial
exhibition, Techno Myanmar'97, sponsored by the Myanmar Industrial
Development Committee (MIDC), is scheduled to be held here from
October 27 to 31.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, which will be launched in cooperation with the
German company, Messe Munchen International based in Singapore,
will include conferences on technology to be participated by local
entrepreneurs and foreign investors in Myanmar, the official paper
The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is said to be aimed at encouraging development
and cooperation between local and foreign entrepreneurs by
providing a new forum for information and trade opportunities and
ongoing projects in the country.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will cover farming technology, construction,
mining, energy, forestry, various fields of light industry and
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The MIDC, a state-run organization consisting of nine key
ministries, held the first international industrial exhibition in
May last year, with the participation of the country's state and
private enterprises and foreign companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
