<DOCNO> XIE19971001.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dini, Gjinushi Discuss Albania's Economic Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Affairs Minister
Lamberto and Albania's parliament speaker Skender Gjinushi today
discussed how to support economic recovery in Albania.
</P>
<P>
In their talks, they laid out priorities for the international
conference to be held here on October 17, which will lay the
groundwork for helping Albania recover economically from four
months of armed unrest earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Dini and Gjinushi agreed that the ministerial conference will
assess initiatives taken by international organizations, start an
international aid program and coordinate bilateral programs for
economic and technical assistance.
</P>
<P>
A week after the Rome conference, donor nations will hold a a
meeting in Brussels to draw up a strategy for aiding economic and
financial reconstruction in the Balkan country.
</P>
<P>
The International Monetary Fund and Albanian leaders have been
discussing what form the international aid program will take.
</P>
<P>
At today's talks, Dini reiterated a call on Albania to continue
on the road to normalization which began with the June 29
elections and return to open political dialogue involving all the
parties elected democratically, an Italian Foreign Ministry
statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian crisis began in mid-January when the collapse of
pyramid investment schemes cost many Albanians their lifelong
savings and led to mass protests.
</P>
<P>
The situation went out of control after armed rebels ransacked
military arsenals and took control of cities throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Peace was finally restored after the Italian-led multinational
peacekeeping force were sent in and elections were held under
international supervision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
