<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassies Hold National Day Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Embassies in Norway,
Austria, Greece and the Netherlands held receptions today to
celebrate the 48th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the receptions were Norwegian Minister
of Trade and Industry Grete Kundsen, Chief Justice of the Supreme
Court Carsten Smith, Governor of the Central Bank Kjell Storvik;
Austrian Minister of Communications, Scientific Research and Arts
Caspar Einem, Secretary of State Peter Wittma, Third President of
the National Council Willi Brauneder; Greek Minister of National
Defence Akis Tsohatzopoulos, Minister of Labor and Social Security
Miltiades Papaioannou; Dutch Minister of Agriculture J. Van
Aertsen; other senior officials and personalities of various
circles of the four countries and overseas Chinese in those
countries.
</P>
<P>
Many foreign guests expressed their congratulations on the
success of the just-concluded 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and the smooth return of Hong Kong
to the motherland. Many of them also extended good wishes for
China's future. 
</P>
