<HEADLINE> Italy, Croatia Sign Protocol on Technological Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Croatia today signed a
protocol on technological cooperation initiatives for the next two
years.
</P>
<P>
The protocol, which covers agriculture, biotechnology and
energy and environment, gives priority to initiatives that favor
the transfer of new technologies to small and medium-sized
businesses, the Italian Foreign Ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here at the first meeting of the
Italian-Croatian Commission on Scientific and Technological
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
It was the latest move taken by the two countries toward
renewing relations between universities, scientific institutions
and research centers from both countries.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation was disrupted by the unrest in the Balkan
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
