<DOCNO> XIE19971001.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fixed Assets Investment Rises in Shanghai's Pudong New Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Fixed assets investment in the
Pudong New Area of Shanghai in the January-August period rose
nearly 46 percent over the same eight-month period last year, to
nearly 21 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
This is partly the result of construction work at some large
local projects like Pudong International Airport, a Sino-American
joint venture, and an integrated circuit plant funded by the
Ministry of Electronics Industry.
</P>
<P>
Average investment for each of the projects this year went up
to 244 million yuan, a big leap from 174 million yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August the area had a total of 109 projects in
operation, 30 of which were added during the preceding
twelve-month period.
</P>
<P>
Increased spending on infrastructure and the industrial sector
was another reason for increasing investment in fixed
assets. Urban infrastructure cost more than 7.2 billion yuan
during the eight-month period, 2.4 times the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
More than 28 percent of investment in the area, 5.9 billion
yuan, was used for industrial projects, and the area put more than
3.9 billion yuan into technological improvements, a 77 percent
rise from the same period in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
