48th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China
(PRC) yesterday evening.
</P>
<P>
Li at the reception extended National Day greetings on behalf
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
the State Council to all Chinese people. Also, he called the
recently concluded 15th CPC National Congress a milestone in the
history of the Party and the country, which he said is bound to
exert a far-reaching impact on China's future development.
</P>
<P>
-- The paper today ran an editorial to celebrate the National
Day. Headlined "Forge ahead with full confidence and pioneering
spirit," the editorial calls 1997 "a year of great significance in
the history of the People's Republic," for it witnessed the smooth
return of Hong Kong to the motherland on July 1 and the great
success of the 15th Party Congress concluded last month.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese leaders joined more than 10,000 people from all
walks of life in Beijing to attend a gala party celebrating the
48th anniversary of the founding of PRC yesterday evening.
</P>
<P>
-- People in the "old revolutionary bases," where CPC gradually
developed before the founding of New China, vowed to strengthen
efforts towards poverty eradication, thus turning a new chapter of
the less developed regions by upholding the banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Like other Beijing-based major newspapers, the sole
national English daily today carried a large front-page story to
celebrate the country's National Day.
</P>
<P>
