<HEADLINE> Francescoli Wins Player of the Year Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan Enzo
Francescoli has been voted Argentina's player of the year for the
third time.
</P>
<P>
The 35-year-old, who plays for Buenos Aires giants River Plate,
was given the annual Golden Ball award by local sports writers,
equalling Diego Maradona's record of three titles.
</P>
<P>
Francescoli also won the award for the 1984-1985 season and
again 10 seasons later.
</P>
<P>
River Plate's Ramon Diaz was named best coach after his team
won last season's national league title. Paraguayan Jose Luis
Chilavert was named the best goalkeeper. 
</P>
