<HEADLINE> Brazil Leave out Edmundo for Morocco Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Edmundo, top scorer in
the Brazilian championship with 15 goals, was left out of Brazil's
squad for next Tuesday's friendly against Morocco.
</P>
<P>
Brazil coach Mario Zagallo said disciplinary problems provided
the reason why the volatile striker had not been called up.
</P>
<P>
Edmundo took on his last appearance for Brazil in the Copa
America final against Bolivia this June when he elbowed an
opponent down.
</P>
<P>
Sao Paulo full-back Serginho was the only uncapped player in a
squad which includes only five foreign-based players.
</P>
<P>
Top players such as Ronaldo and Roberto Carlos were left out
because they have already used up the quota of five full
internationals for which their European clubs are obliged to
release them in a calendar year. 
