<HEADLINE> Ivanisevic Crashes out at First Hurdle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZURICH, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Goran Ivanisevic
crashed out in the first round with a straight sets defeat by
Slovakia's Karol Kucera at the Swiss indoor championships on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The big-serving Croat, ranked eighth in the world, was brushed
aside 6-4, 6-3 in just 74 minutes by the world number 32 Kucera.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Carlos Moya of Spain, trailing 4-2 in the decisive
set, eked out a 6-4, 3-6, 6-4 win over 19-year-old German wild
card Tommy Haas.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov had no such problems as he cruised
smoothly into the second round with 6-1, 7-6 win over Swiss
qualifier Lorenzo Manta.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Tim Henman, aiming for a third tournament victory
this season, disposed of Germany's Marc-Kevin Goellner 7-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The 1994 title holder Wayne Ferreira of South Africa also won
his first round match, slipping past New Zealand's Brett Stevens
6-7, 6-1, 7-6. 
</P>
