<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Smaller company shares on
Wall Street pushed further into record highs today, but most
popular stock measures fell slightly after the Federal Reserve, as
expected, decided to leave interest rates unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 46.17 to 7,945.26.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 9-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 586.79 million
shares, higher than that in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 6.06 to 947.28, the
NYSE composite index fell 1.75 to 497.23, and the Nasdaq composite
index fell 9.31 to 1,685.67.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 2.51 to 453.82, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 4.60 to 699.26.
</P>
<P>
Most broad-market indicators also edged lower after today's Fed
meeting ended with no change in the central bank's key lending
rates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
