<HEADLINE> David Stephen Appointed Head of Somalia Political Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today designated David Stephen as head of the United
Nations Political Office for Somalia (UNPOS) effective on October
1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Stephen will assume duties on October 9 in Nairobi, Kenya,
where the office is currently located in view of security
conditions in Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Stephen, who is a national of the United Kingdom, is at present
chief of the Executive Office of the Secretary-General. Between
1996 and February 1997 he was director of the United Nations Human
Rights Verification Mission in Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
Prior to his Guatemala appointment, Stephen served in the
Executive Office of the Secretary-General since 1992. A specialist
in Latin American Government Studies with considerable experience
in immigration, refugee and development issues in that region, he
also previously headed the Latin American regional office of the
International University Exchange Fund. He also served as special
adviser to the secretary of state for foreign and commonwealth
affairs, director of the United Kingdom's immigrant advisory
service and director of corporate relations of the Commonwealth
Development Corporation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
